# data-processing-models

Core Data Models:

1. GDPR Processing Activities
Path: src/models/processing-activities.ts

Key Entities:
- Processing Activity Records (Art. 30 GDPR)
- Data Categories and Special Categories 
- Processing Purposes
- Legal Basis Tracking
- Cross-border Transfer Details
- Data Subject Categories
- Recipients and Third Parties

2. Data Flow Mapping
Path: src/models/data-flows.ts

Model Structure:
- Data Flow Nodes (Systems, Applications, Third Parties)
- Data Flow Connections
- Transfer Types (Internal, External, Cross-border)
- Data Categories In Transit
- Security Controls Applied
- Processing Activities Links

3. Legal Basis Registry
Path: src/models/legal-basis.ts

Key Elements:
- Legal Basis Categories (Consent, Contract, Legal Obligation, etc.)
- Processing Purpose Mapping
- Data Category Requirements  
- Retention Period Rules
- Documentation Links
- Status Tracking

4. Data Protection Impact Assessments
Path: src/models/dpia.ts

Assessment Structure:
- Processing Operations
- Necessity & Proportionality Tests
- Risk Assessments
- Mitigation Measures
- DPO Consultations
- Prior Consultation Status

Key Relationships:
- Processing Activities link to Legal Basis entries
- Data Flows map to Processing Activities
- DPIAs reference Processing Activities
- Legal Basis entries connect to multiple Processing Activities

Schema Enforcement:
- Required fields validation
- Relationship integrity checks
- Status progression rules
- Documentation requirements

